Rent-A-Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucamala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 10:46:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> i agree to atwork and i also think a guild who's up for a dragon must post their intend at least 24 hours before the deadline, if they do not they should be considered passing. After all 24 hours is not really enough time to organise it anyway and those who really do the raid post it sooner usually, so this would reduce lost time due to non-existing guilds <p>Camala<BR>
Gemchopper<BR>
Warriors of Wrath<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 548<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 10:53:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.yellowspine.com/images/jestur01.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> I'm leaning toward the only if repoped is unannounced.  Need a really good argument from someone to change my mind.  Going to wait to vote to give someone a chance to give their view otherwise. <p><b>Redspine Bladeslinger - 56th Myrmidon</b><br>
Jestur - 50th Cleric Gnome with Attitude! <br>
Whitefange - 17th Shaman<br>
Guild Biatch <i>eerr</i> Leader of Lost Adventurers<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1685<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 10:56:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> I don't think this rule is necessary. Nagafen failed more than Vox before Kunark, and those players didn't have as good gear as the current Vox raiders do, didn't have access to 50+ buffs, and didn't need an eternity to get enough people. I could get together 36 people for a raid even if I didn't ask a single member of my guild, frankly if this is allowed it'll soon degenerate into people reserving the ghoul lord 1 year in advance then flaming anyone who goes there because they reserved it. Vox is being frequently wasted now, she'll just be killed even less with this, there is no reason to reward sloppy organization. <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucreloneraincaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crelone Raincaller</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wah.nu/Mischief/Crelone.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 1:18:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1>   Well Nillon I don't really see that as a fair statement. I have seen some very organized raids fail due to bad luck and some raids that shouldn't have suceeded do also due to the right thing at the right time happening. <br>
  One of the raids I heard raves about the way it was organized was the UoJ raid a few days ago and it failed due to some really bad luck. I truely believe had they had one more day to take the shot they would have won. So sorry I totally disagree with ya here. <br>
 Personally I think those of us at 53+ should really let those that it effects decide.<br>
<br>
Crelone Raincaller<br>
53rd Ranger of Brell<br>
Blood Inferno <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1549<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 1:44:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> Just because I'm 54 doesn't mean I wouldn't have a perspective to add on how it is going.  I agree with most of what Nillon posted.  I don't think it should be extended.  As it is, I don't feel like I can even sign up for the dragon because the waiting list is too long.  I have other things to do with my guild so I haven't really bitched about this before.  Sure I could have put my guild on the list a few months ago so when this came up my guild would be at the right age.  They are finally at the right age and uhh..to sign up now ..they will be past 52 probably by the time our time came up.<br>
<br>
I don't have sympathy really for people who get on a long list like this and then have trouble finding support.   Please don't read anything into that last statement.  If anything I could go along the lines of what Redspine said and that is with an unplanned outage.  If you are leading the raid, then you hold the responsibility of knowing the stage of the dragon before your time is up, when is the last patch going to happen, who has the dragon now, when are they planning to take it down, doing the math to see when your day MAY come up and then getting the support behind you. <br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucreloneraincaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crelone Raincaller</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.wah.nu/Mischief/Crelone.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 2:13:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> Saph,<br>
 Being in a similar situation with my guild I understand what you are saying. However, even given that amount of time and paying attention you always get cancels and no shows even from the people you count on and have told you they will be there. Real Life happens =0) Also my big problem is not with server patched I have 48 hours. My problem is mostly with someone in front of me waits till day 2 fails and doesn't get off the pot untill Zesty kicks them off by then I've lost 8-12 hours of planning or in some cases a day. <br>
  I also believe with the extra 24 people will kill her more not less. Yes I understand you lose a day, but if Guild A kills her under the 72 hour rule first time out then it's 7 days till repop (total 10 days). If under the 48 (this has been the case I've seen) guild A tries dies waits gives up or gets kicked by Zesty in the pants. Guild B tries follows same pattern but only really had 36 hours to plan rinse/repeat. The dragon ends up going down but only because she/he got patched not because someone killed her.(total days 14 or patch)<br>
  Personally I could really care less how long the lists are we will plan it, get there, and kill whatever said mob is and have fun doing it.<br>
<br>
Again just MHO<br>
<br>
Crelone  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukuanshankein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KuanShanKein</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://comunidad.ciudad.com.ar/ciudadanos/maverik/links/ferro.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 260<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 3:37:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://comunidad.ciudad.com.ar/ciudadanos/maverik/kuan.jpg WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> 48 hours is more than enough. I thought we were trying to make lists shorter.<br>
<br>
Kuan. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 460<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 10:10:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> The lists may be getting rotated faster with the 48 hour rule.  But particularly with Vox, there is little success.  It's depressing, even to me, to see that many rotations happen and Vox not get taken down.  I would like to give people an extra day and better their chances at taking down these dragons.<br>
<br>
When UoJ did their Vox raid, they had what they needed, they had very bad luck.  If they would have had another day, they would have taken her down, no doubt.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
