 ---</b></font><font size="2"><br></font><font size="1">Updated 1/28/2001</font></font></font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 11:01:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> Much like with the venril rotation, quite a few of the names should take a long hard look to see if they have the manpower (among friends and guildmates) to take down these Dragons.<br>
<br>
I think that we are seeing many guilds hoping to get oodles of signups so that they can claim their very own pally book, cof, or dragon scale... I think that if the complaint is that they can't get a raid organized in that short a period of time, that they should perhaps look at their guild and figure out if they *really* have what it takes to kill a dragon.<br>
<br>
There's still what? 15-20 guilds running Vox, perhaps if some tried an alliance with another small guild on the list they might actually kill one.<br>
<br>
Ps. When was the last time Vox fell? Harpers raid a month or two back?<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
52nd Enchantress<br>
Quorum Angelus <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/starlord51180/girl_09.jpg"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaennenfizzlewhiff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaennen Fizzlewhiff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 374<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/31/01 11:30:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> Can I ask why those who are high 50's (who cannot do these dragons) are voting?   <p><br>
