Bane of the Stone Hive Bixies<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucartumandua.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cartumandua</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tunare's Tough Love</span><br>  Posts: 509<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/1/01 12:16:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> <br>
Why are we expressing an opinion?<br>
<br>
Because most of us did Vox before we got too high/verant nerfed it.<br>
<br>
As such we have a reasonable perspective on it, and what it takes.<br>
<br>
My feeling is that if you've signed up, you ought to know where your raid crew is going to come from.  As you get closer to the time, you ought to be chatting with those folks to make sure they'll try to make it.  Plan for more than you need.<br>
<br>
If 48 hours isn't enough, then I'd be surprised if 72 was.<br>
<br>
I don't think extending the time helps those who are waiting and have done the prep for their raids.<br>
<br>
Yes, I know, even well prepared raids fail sometimes because of bad luck.  Oh well.  There's always next time.<br>
<br>
