 <B>Dynin Vifargent</B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/1/01 5:10:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/G36206?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> First I think our previous discussion of extension to 72 hours does not include a raid following a previously successful raid.  Adun has pointed out that.<br>
<br>
Second I have seen some people who don't even seem to know how the raid forums work requested to get into Naggy/Vox rotation.  This is not good and I think those raids have good chance of failure.  I think the raid organisers should have at least done several Naggy/Vox raids with some of them successful before getting into rotation.  However I don't know how it's possible to enforce this but let's make it at least a guideline to those raid organisers. <p>Ganaddor Saolinlight<BR>
Lvl 52 disciple of the Shaolin Temple<BR>
<BR>
Dikamin Serilisknight<BR>
Semi-Retired 51th Paladin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvaal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaal</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 256<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/1/01 8:41:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ***DISCUSSION*** -- Vox/Nag time limit proposal</span><hr size=1> I agree with 1 and 3 but not 2 and 4, I think 72 hours after a failed raid and an unplanned server outage are fine, but for planned server outages and after successful raids, only 48 hours is required, because you know you are next after a successful raid so you will be ready. <p>Vaal Khon'Elvair <BR>
